1 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES - FLOOR VERSION
2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
4 HOUSE BILL 4321 By: Kendrix of the House
5 and
6 Alvord of the Senate
7
8 AS INTRODUCED
9 An Act relating to the Elevator Safety Act; amending
59 O.S. 2021, Section 3023.4, which relates to
10 enforcing the Elevator Safety Act; prohibiting
retroactive application without safety exemption; and
11 providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 3023.4, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 3023.4. A. It shall be the duty of the Department of
18 Labor to develop an enforcement program which will ensure compliance
19 with regulations and requirements referenced in this chapter. An
20 enforcement program may include, but is not limited to, regulations
21 for identification of property locations which are subject to the
22 regulations and requirements; issuing notifications to violating
23 property owners or operators; random on-site inspections and tests
24 on existing installations; witnessing periodic inspections and
HB4321 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 test ing in order to ensure satisfactory performance by licensed
2 persons, sole proprietors, firms or corporations; and assisting in
3 the development of public awareness programs. The Department shall
4 not retroactively apply new rules and standards to existing
5 structures unless the Department produces written findings,
6 supported by documented evidence, that the structure presents
7 obvious safety hazards.
8 B. Any person may request an investigation into an alleged
9 violation of this chapter by giving notice to the Department of
10 Labor of such violation or danger. The notice shall be in writing,
11 shall set forth with reasonable particularity the grounds for the
12 notice, and shall be signed by the person making the request.
13 C. Upon receipt of a notification, if the Commissioner
14 determines that there are reasonable grounds to believe that a
15 violation or danger exists, the Commissioner shall cause to be made
16 an investigation in accordance with this chapter as soon as
17 practicable to determine if such violation or danger exists. If the
18 Commissioner determines that there are no reasonable grounds to
19 believe that a violation or danger exists, the Department of Labor
20 shall notify the party in writing of such determination.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
22
23 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON COMMERCE AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT
OVERSIGHT, dated 02/26/2026 - DO PASS.
